.
</emphasis>
Posterior ocellus separated from eye about 1.4
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
its maximum diameter. Distance between hind ocelli about once maximum diameter of posterior ocellus. Clypeus about 1.9
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as broad as medially long. Malar space about 0.58
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as basal mandibular width. Antenna with 29 flagellomeres; flagellum only slightly enlarged subapically; flagellomeres from f14(15) to apex flattened ventrally; f1 about 6.0
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
long as its maximum width. 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">Mesosoma</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Pronotum mostly smooth and shiny, shallowly strigose punctate dorsally. Mesopleuron shallowly strigose punctate dorsally and centrally close to mesopleural fovea, elsewhere smooth and shiny; sternaulus with weak transverse keels. Metapleuron transversely strigose punctate. Posterior transverse carina forming low lateral crests. Areolet about 0.67
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as high as wide, about 0.7
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as high as abscissa of vein 2m-cu above bulla. Hind wing with vein cu-a 0.64
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as first abscissa of CU. 
